get_clock_network_objects(25.10)              get_clock_network_objects(25.10)

Name
       get_clock_network_objects - Returns the cells or pins that exist in the
       clock network of the specified clocks

Syntax
       get_clock_network_objects

       [-help]

       [-clocks <clock_list>]

       [-type {cell | pin}]

       Returns the cells or pins that exist in the clock network of the speci-
       fied clocks.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -clocks <clock_list>
              Returns  the  cells  or pins present in the clock network of the
              specified clock(s).

       -type {cell | pin}
              Returns the specified cells or pins in the clock network.

       Examples
              * The following command returns the pins present  in  the  clock
                network of all the clocks:

                get_clock_network_objects

              * The following command returns the pins that exist in the clock
                network of CLK and CLK2 clocks:

                get_clock_network_objects -clocks {CLK CLK2}

              * The  following  command  returns  the  cells that exist in the
                clock network of CLK clock.

                get_clock_network_objects -clocks {CLK} -type cell

